===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} ''[[oolithus]]'', from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|ᾠο-||oo-}} + {{m|grc|λίθος||stone}}, corresponding to {{confix|oo|lith|lang=en}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈəʊəlɪθ/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{label|en|geology}} A spherical [[granule]] of which [[oolite]] is composed, formed by concentric accretion of thin layers of a mineral around a core. Calcium carbonate ([[limestone]]) is the most common mineral that forms '''ooliths''', but they may also form from other minerals such as [[dolomite]] and [[silica]].
# {{label|en|rare}} [[oolite|Oolite]].

